29/11/2007
ATHENS, Greece --Working together, the police forces of Croatia, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) and Greece have smashed an international drug trafficking ring and seized 80kg of cocaine. The stash, shipped from an unspecified South American country, was discovered inside a container at the Greek port of Piraeus. One person was arrested in Greece, while six Bosnians and two Croats were arrested in BiH and Croatia. The drugs were reportedly destined for Western Europe. (AP, UPI - 28/11/07) 
